<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-660-328  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 660 328.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  Sept 7 1989 n1180 p20(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Trench war for control of the skies. (United Kingdom's air defencesystem)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Collins, Tony.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The United Kingdom's main underground air defense command site inBuckinghamshire is equipped with virtually everything NATO and theRoyal Air Force could need, except the computerized command andcontrol system for which the bunker was built.andP;  It is supposed tobe the home of the UKAIR CCIS command and control (C2) systemdesigned to improve the strategy of air operations in the NATO UKair regions during times of hostility.andP;  The contract was awardedto ICL in Apr 1987, with promise of a fully operational system by1991.andP;  ICL renegotiated the price, an increase of 10 percent overthe original 37 million pounds sterling, in early Sep 1989.andP;  Thenew delivery date is early 1992.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   ICL PLC (contracts).andO;Topic:     United KingdomAir ForceControl SystemsCommand and Control SystemsContracts.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>